a:r.a:t: The purpose of this request is to present a high level overview and recommendations on upstream data preprocessing prior to research activity.
To prevent getting personal data privacy exposure
To pre-treat known data issues upstream
To enable clean and free of PII data readiness for public facing research
Recommendation for Raw Data Pre-Processing for Known Data Issues
Ensure that All Raw Data Is Anonymized
Ensure that no legally defined personally identifiable information ever get to the research stage
Replace identifiable personal data with hashed id’s
Mapping tables that can be used to identify personal users should be made unavailable to researchers
Ensure System Generated Values are Documented

If special coding was used to automatically assign some known values to some table columns, they should be documented in a mapping table for researchers to properly create appropriate imputation for analysis and machine learning.
Ensure unexpected negative values are documented, separated in the data and not aggregated together
Add anomaly detection flags to the data to raise awareness of some common resolvable data issues
Some of the raw data have coding in them that may not reflect the normal data collection value ranges.
ER34144A OFUM TOTAL LABOR INCOME- IMPUTED
ER34143 G34 AMT SOC SEC RCD:
ER34144C OFUM TOTAL ASSET INCOME – IMPUTED
ER34144D OFUM TOTAL TAXABLE INCOME – IMPUTED
The Following Known Data Issue Detection Methods Can Be Implemented
Appropriate for relatively independent time series data
Not very appropriate if there are interactions between the data generation process
Cooks statistics detects outliers using more than one columns
Cooks statistics may not be appropriate if the data series are relatively independent.
